Sub Pop will be releasing Iron and Wine - Norfolk 6/20/05, a limited, live CD, on April 18, Record Store Day 2009. The 18 track disc was recorded during the Woman King tour and features a full band.
The disc can only be found at participating record stores and at this time, will not be made available on the Iron and Wine or Sub Pop sites.

This will be the second annual Record Store Day and is a celebration of the unique culture surrounding over 700 independently owned record stores in the USA, and hundreds of international stores. This is the one day that all of the independently owned record stores come together with artists to celebrate the art of music. Iron and Wine is very excited to be involved in Record Store Day.
A Record Store Day participating store is defined as a physical retailer whose product line consists of at least 50% music retail, whose company is not publicly traded and whose ownership is at least 70% located in the state of operation.
